race.comment: SHANGHAI VENTURE (12) was in the money two starts back at Sale but was unable to repeat the effort last time when ninth, beaten 4 lengths, at Moonee Valley over 1200m. Faces an easier assignment so she is likely to play a big role. KAGEMUSHA (5) was put away after a plain debut but has run two nice races this time in, including a last start win. Significantly, the first-up run was on a Heavy track and he was only narrowly beaten. DRONE ATTACK (6) drifted back from her wide draw when resuming last time then hit the line hard to finish third at Echuca over 1200m. Will be running on late again. EBONY FIGHTER (7) last appeared five-and-a-half months ago when she finished 5.5 lengths from the winner in fifth over 1400m at Sandown-Hillside. In the mix fresh.
